body: ## Steps to Reproduce 1. I cloned [flutter/plugins](https://github.com/flutter/plugins). 2. I opened `packages/firebase_database` in IntelliJ. 3. I got analysis errors after running `packages get`: I attempted to fix this by double clicking on `example/pubspec.yaml` and hitting `packages get`, but based on the terminal prompt (`Running 'flutter packages get' in firebase_database...`), it looks like it just ran on the root, not the nested package. Right clicking on `example/pubspec.yaml` and clicking `Flutter > Packages Get` did the same thing. I ended up having to navigate with the command line to resolve this analysis warning. ## Version info ``` [‚úì] Flutter (on Mac OS X 10.12.4 16E195, channel alpha) ‚Ä¢ Flutter at /Users/matanl/git/flutter ‚Ä¢ Framework revision 00214fa7bd (3 weeks ago), 2017-05-16 09:31:35 -0700 ‚Ä¢ Engine revision f99d3ef108 ‚Ä¢ Tools Dart version 1.23.0-dev.11.11 [‚úì] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK 25.0.3) ‚Ä¢ Android SDK at /Users/matanl/Library/Android/sdk ‚Ä¢ Platform android-25, build-tools 25.0.3 ‚Ä¢ Java binary at: /Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jre/jdk/Contents/Home/bin/java ‚Ä¢ Java version: OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_112-release-b06) [‚úì] iOS toolchain - develop for iOS devices (Xcode 8.2.1) ‚Ä¢ Xcode at /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer ‚Ä¢ Xcode 8.2.1, Build version 8C1002 ‚Ä¢ ios-deploy 1.9.1 ‚Ä¢ CocoaPods version 1.2.1 [‚úì] Android Studio (version 2.3) ‚Ä¢ Android Studio at /Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents ‚Ä¢ Gradle version 3.2 ‚Ä¢ Java version: OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_112-release-b06) [‚úì] IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate Edition (version 2017.1.3) ‚Ä¢ Dart plugin version 171.4424.63 ‚Ä¢ Flutter plugin version 14.0 [‚úì] Connected devices ‚Ä¢ None ```

comment_data.body: Ah, talking to @devoncarew, this looks like a bug on our end.  We're not handling nesting when calling out to `flutter packages get`.

This issue is more that IntelliJ wasn't using the closest nested pubspec.yaml. That one is that the command-line dartanalyzer doesn't use the same context creation logic as the analysis server (and the analysis server is the one we want to emulate here).
